1
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:12,490
'Tonight, I speak German...'

2
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:14,250
Vorsprung durch!

3
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,290
'.. the German speaks English...'

4
00:00:16,340 --> 00:00:18,050
Go out, go out, go out!

5
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:22,370
'.. and Matt takes a tour of London
with superstar wheel man Ken Block.'

6
00:00:22,420 --> 00:00:24,490
Oh! Westminster Bridge!

7
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:42,130
Hello, and welcome to Top Gear.

8
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:44,930
This is it, the wait is
over. Tonight is the night.

9
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:48,810
Yes, the night where more cars go sideways

10
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:50,810
than ever before on Top Gear.

11
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:55,330
No, no. No, that's not
what I'm talking about. No.

12
00:00:55,380 --> 00:00:59,730
I'm talking about you guys
finally getting to see Chris

13
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:02,050
enjoy his breakfast twice.

14
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:08,570
Once on the way down and once
again on the way back up.

15
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:10,490
Can we just get this over with, please?

16
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:13,420
Sure, yeah. Let's roll the Audi R8 film.

17
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:19,970
Here is the brand-new R8 2.0,

18
00:01:20,020 --> 00:01:22,560
and it's gunning for the big boys.

19
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:28,770
Cost -- £135,000.

20
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:32,170
Engine -- the V10 from
the Lamborghini Huracan.

21
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:35,620
Horsepower -- over 600.

22
00:01:40,860 --> 00:01:43,850
And there's no cheaty turbo charging here,

23
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:49,340
which means you can rev this
engine all the way to 8,700 rpm.

24
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:56,210
Even the slightest tickle of that
accelerator delivers all that power

25
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:58,660
right to the back of your head.

26
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:02,850
0-60 in 3.2 seconds.

27
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:07,730
And she will not run out of
puff until she hits 205mph,

28
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:10,010
which makes her the
fastest, most powerful,

29
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:13,250
road going Audi of all time.

30
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,660
Vorsprung durch. Have some of that!

31
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:24,130
The engine might be supercar old school,

32
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:26,410
but everything else about the R8 is

33
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:29,420
reassuringly state-of-the-art.

34
00:02:31,620 --> 00:02:34,930
There's aluminium and carbon
fibre all over the shop,

35
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:38,450
which makes it a bit lighter,
but a lot stiffer than before.

36
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:42,250
And as far as looks go, it's
completely an R8 still, obviously.

37
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:47,130
However, it's just subtly so
much sharper and better sculpted,

38
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:50,660
miles better looking. I love it.

39
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:55,130
Physical dials? No chance.

40
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:58,610
The entire dash is a
high-def widescreen telly

41
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:01,330
that can be configured as you desire.

42
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:05,530
And then there's the stuff you can't see.

43
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:10,170
Under your fingertips here is a
seven-speed, twin-clutch gearbox,

44
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:14,090
changing gear faster than you can
say, "Does it come in manual?"

45
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,840
Which it doesn't, by the way.

46
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:22,330
And because it's a bonkers fast Audi,

47
00:03:22,380 --> 00:03:25,250
naturally it has to have four-wheel drive.

48
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:28,130
This, though, is especially
clever four-wheel drive

49
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:31,970
which can shove 100% of the
engine's power front or back

50
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:34,690
depending on which end wants it most.

51
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:40,170
Every single second this R8 is
making a gazillion calculations

52
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,170
based on information drawn
from hundreds of sensors

53
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:47,740
that help it to decide exactly
where to push and what to shove.

54
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:54,610
One of the results of which is that
it grips so well through the corners

55
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:58,530
your internal organs will
have to apologise to each other

56
00:03:58,580 --> 00:03:59,810
quite a lot.

57
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,600
Here we go again.

58
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:12,490
So, the R8 will change gear for you.

59
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:14,290
It will alter the suspension stiffness

60
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:16,450
and steering response for you.

61
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,290
It will decide how to
divvy up the power for you.

62
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:22,370
ALL to give you the optimum performance.

63
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:26,610
There's no doubt that the
R8 is a brilliant car.

64
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:28,890
An amazing bit of kit,

65
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:35,450
but is it just a bit too friendly
to be a genuine supercar?

66
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:37,770
Or does it have a dark side?

67
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:42,850
To test whether the Audi computers
have removed the V10's venom,

68
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:45,250
we've come to one of the most extreme,

69
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:49,010
intimidating race circuits on the planet.

70
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,980
Laguna Seca.

71
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:55,100
Home to the infamous Corkscrew.

72
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:02,170
A high-speed descending helter
skelter over a blind crest

73
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:05,220
that throws you into a
sheer 30-metre drop.

74
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:10,690
Clearly there was only one
person in Top Gear's arsenal

75
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,680
to take to the wheel.

76
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,700
Sabine Schmitz.

77
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:19,170
- Sab...
- Hm?

78
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,050
How about a challenge?

79
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:23,290
Challenge? What do you mean?

80
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:28,690
- Your brain versus Audi's
brain. Two flying laps. - Mm-hm.

81
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,890
First lap, the car's in control.

82
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:33,970
All the computers, all the race
aids on, gearbox in automatic.

83
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:37,370
- You're just a driving monkey. OK?
- Yeah, OK.

84
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,690
Second lap,

85
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:42,610
you're in charge of
everything, gearbox in manual.

86
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:46,540
- Sabine versus the machine.
- Oh, cool.

87
00:05:47,660 --> 00:05:49,220
Let's go.

88
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,650
'First lap, dynamic mode.

89
00:05:56,700 --> 00:06:00,170
'That means all of the R8's
driver's aids are on --

90
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:03,530
'launch control, dynamic
steering, track spec damping

91
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:05,010
'and traction control,

92
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:08,610
'faster throttle response
and a quicker gear change.'

93
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:12,530
Three, two, one. Go!

94
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,410
I'm just a monkey behind the wheel!

95
00:06:15,460 --> 00:06:17,060
I do nothing!

96
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:22,050
It's shifting itself.

97
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:25,100
Whoo!

98
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:28,720
Corner number three.

99
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:31,730
No gear shift at all.

100
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:35,250
Are you still there?

101
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:38,210
We're going on the hill. Corkscrew!

102
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:41,420
That was fun.

103
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:46,370
The car has everything under control.

104
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:48,560
Coming to the final bend.

105
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:50,570
Oh, baby!

106
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:52,220
Home straight.

107
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,970
Oh, slow down, Sabine, please.

108
00:06:56,020 --> 00:06:57,450
You need some fresh air?

109
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,970
Oh, [BLEEP].

110
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:00,970
[BLEEP! BLEEP! BLEEP!]

111
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:05,090
'After putting a few pounds in the
swear jar it was time for lap two.

112
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:08,490
'This time, all driver's aids off.'

113
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:10,450
OK, 1.46.78 to beat.

114
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,450
Can Sabine beat the Audi machine?

115
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,460
In three, two, one. Go!

116
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:23,570
This is the real deal now.

117
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:25,290
Hairpin bend.

118
00:07:25,340 --> 00:07:27,610
Go on, Sabine.

119
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:31,090
Feels better from a passenger
point of view, if that matters.

120
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:32,690
Yes, corner number three.

121
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,530
Going well.

122
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:36,730
Yeah!

123
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:38,520
Come on, Sabine.

124
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:42,970
Yeah!

125
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:45,450
- Feels smoother.
- Good traction.

126
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,490
Up the hill. Come on.

127
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,610
All you can see is sky!

128
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:54,680
Oh, much quicker into
the Corkscrew this time.

129
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:00,060
Hold on tight to your balls, sonny!

130
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:03,450
- Ah!
- Hey!

131
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,700
My stomach wants a divorce.

132
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,770
Two more corners left.

133
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:13,220
This is great stuff. Yes!

134
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,890
Very late breaking into the last corner.

135
00:08:16,940 --> 00:08:18,410
Come on, Sabine.

136
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:21,560
You can do it. Sideways
into the home straight.

137
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:26,660
- Go on, Sabine.
- Here is the finish line.

138
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,370
Whoo!

139
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:32,130
Stop! Stop! Stop!

140
00:08:32,180 --> 00:08:34,050
Stop! Please, stop!

141
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:39,970
Go out, go out, go out!

142
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,050
Why is it red?

143
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,410
Strawberries. For breakfast.

144
00:08:56,820 --> 00:09:01,570
The new Audi R8 and
Sabine Schmitz, everyone!

145
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:10,450
Who did beat the machine by
seven seconds. Seven seconds.

146
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:13,580
Yeah! Thank you very much.

147
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:21,250
So, Sabine, the Audi R8 V10 Plus,
Audi's fastest road car ever.

148
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,730
A hit or a miss?

149
00:09:22,780 --> 00:09:25,490
I like the suspension, I like the
response of the steering wheel,

150
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:28,010
I like the power and the
brakes. Everything perfect.

151
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:31,010
I have a little problem with
all that technics inside,

152
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:32,450
you know the computer stuff.

153
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,810
Doesn't work so easy, you
really have to think about it,

154
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:37,850
- what you're doing. - So,
thumbs up? - Thumbs up.

155
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:40,970
I love it, but I'm not so
sure about strawberry boy.

156
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,100
I'm not here.

157
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:49,010
OK. Didn't say you were.

158
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:52,610
Now it's time to hand the R8
over to our tame racing driver.

159
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,890
Some say...

160
00:09:53,940 --> 00:09:57,130
es ist der Mann der
auch ein Rennfahrer ist.

161
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:02,570
Er hat zwei... Fuchse!

162
00:10:05,420 --> 00:10:07,970
Oh, it gets me every time. I tell you.

163
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:11,730
- OK, all we know is he's called...
- .. the Stig!

164
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:14,970
All right. Let's do this.

165
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:17,290
Off the line, the Audi R8 V10 Plus.

166
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:18,930
Italian heart, German suit.

167
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:21,650
Stig, with all the computers
firmly switched off,

168
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,610
just like Sabine, of course.

169
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:25,930
Up to the first corner and
that's very, very tidy,

170
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:28,180
nip and tuck from the Stig.

171
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,610
Stealthy focus, focus stealthy.

172
00:10:31,660 --> 00:10:33,450
Immaculate through Chicago.

173
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,930
Oh, so precise. Oh, so accurate.

174
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:37,570
Very Teutonic.

175
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:39,250
Into Hammerhead now.

176
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:41,530
Will there be any oversteer whatsoever?

177
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,970
Of course there won't.

178
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:45,530
The R8's four-wheel drive
system keeping everything

179
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,530
pointed in the right direction.

180
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,880
Time to open up the taps
now and step on that gas.

181
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:56,180
Up to the tyre wall, then.

182
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:59,050
Bit of a slide on the exit there.

183
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:00,770
Second-to-last corner.

184
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:02,930
Stig stamping on those
carbon ceramic brakes.

185
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:05,580
Still no dramas. Why would there be?

186
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:09,170
Round Gambon clean as
a choirboy's conscience

187
00:11:09,220 --> 00:11:11,160
and across the line.

188
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:18,010
So, we have the car here
and we have the time here.

189
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:21,370
The Audi R8 V10 Plus,
basically a Lamborghini Huracan

190
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:23,970
dressed for dinner as opposed
to ragging it around the track,

191
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:25,290
so, it should be pretty close.

192
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:27,370
There's the Lamborghini Huracan at 1.15.8.

193
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:29,890
And it is... 1.15.7.

194
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:31,610
There they are.

195
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,290
Happy together.

196
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:37,940
OK. OK.

197
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:41,730
Now, here's the film that's
made all of us the most jealous,

198
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:43,770
because we didn't get to make it.

199
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:47,180
Driving the new Ferrari F12
tdf, it's that damn Chris Harris.

200
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,320
- Hate that guy.
- Yeah.

201
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:16,780
This is the Ferrari 250 GT
Berlinetta Tour de France.

202
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:21,850
It's a car named after the legendary race.

203
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:23,210
No, not that one.

204
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:24,860
The other one.

205
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:28,180
The Tour de France Automobile.

206
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:33,810
They called it the toughest
car race in history.

207
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:35,970
An entire lap of France.

208
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:41,490
4,000-odd gruelling miles over
ten days on road, track and dirt.

209
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:46,700
The Tour de France made the Le Mans
24 Hours look like a Sunday fun run.

210
00:12:49,540 --> 00:12:51,650
It ran for nearly a century,

211
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:54,530
but its glory days were
the end of the 1950s,

212
00:12:54,580 --> 00:12:57,730
where this Ferrari 250
Tour de France cleaned up,

213
00:12:57,780 --> 00:13:00,370
winning every year it competed.

214
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:05,220
Only 77 were ever made and
this one is worth £5 million.

215
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:10,370
They were easy to drive long-distance.

216
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,650
They were reliable.

217
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,370
But they were also quick.

218
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:15,780
This one can do 160mph.

219
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:23,100
Which is thanks to a three-litre
V12 producing 250 horsepower.

220
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:27,820
Which, by 1950s' standards, was a lot.

221
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:31,250
What's it like into this hairpin?

222
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,930
Second. Heel and toe. First.

223
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,170
Wow!

224
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:35,610
Bit of understeer.

225
00:13:35,660 --> 00:13:37,130
Get on the gas early.

226
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:38,370
Grab second.

227
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:40,360
Listen to the noise!

228
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,410
My first day in the job.

229
00:13:44,460 --> 00:13:49,010
Can't believe they've given me a
£5 million Ferrari to throw around.

230
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:52,410
Wouldn't make the best introduction to
the BBC insurance department, would it?

231
00:13:52,460 --> 00:13:55,000
"Hi. Yeah, Chris here. New bloke."

232
00:13:57,580 --> 00:14:00,170
The Tour de France race
didn't just run on road.

233
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,930
They'd also stop off for
a blast around any track

234
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:04,610
they found along the way.

235
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:06,600
Tracks like this one.

236
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,660
Circuit Paul Ricard.

237
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,200
Fast...

238
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,370
.. technical...

239
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,850
.. and boasting one of the
longest straights of any

240
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,840
track on the planet.

241
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:27,420
Just the place, then, to let
the old girl off the leash.

242
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:32,320
My first chance to open it up.

243
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,340
Yes.

244
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:37,090
Doesn't get any better.

245
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:39,340
That engine, that gearbox.

246
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:44,490
It's really hard not to
imagine yourself as some

247
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:47,140
gentleman racer from the late '50s.

248
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:49,840
What a life to lead.

249
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:52,770
Whoa, bit of oversteer.

250
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,980
So good was the 250 TDF that when
it reached racing retirement...

251
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:02,810
.. Ferrari retired its name too.

252
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:11,260
Now, 50 years later, the
Tour de France is back.

253
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:17,060
Whoa-ho-ho, ho-ho!

254
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:21,220
Welcome to the Ferrari F12 tdf.

255
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:29,820
