Good air! Excellent air
for such a big guy.

743
00:37:53,220 --> 00:37:56,210
- Right, Tyre Wall...
- This is the one, this is the one.

744
00:37:56,260 --> 00:37:57,570
Whoo!

745
00:37:57,620 --> 00:38:00,060
Look at that, look at that!

746
00:38:01,140 --> 00:38:05,240
16 fights undefeated, will he
retain his perfect record here?

747
00:38:07,220 --> 00:38:10,930
Bouncing into the last corner,
big chunk of grass there

748
00:38:10,980 --> 00:38:13,690
and he's over the line!

749
00:38:13,740 --> 00:38:15,530
Great drive. That is a great drive.

750
00:38:15,580 --> 00:38:18,850
- Well done, well done, well done.
- That's a great drive.

751
00:38:18,900 --> 00:38:20,050
That's a great drive.

752
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:23,370
- What do we think?
- May the best man win.

753
00:38:23,420 --> 00:38:26,210
- May the best man win.
- That's fine, cos it's you.

754
00:38:26,260 --> 00:38:29,730
- That's what I'm saying, deep down.
- That was a great drive.

755
00:38:29,780 --> 00:38:33,410
I thought they were both great
drives, very, very good.

756
00:38:33,460 --> 00:38:37,010
Kevin, to go top, 1.53.9 to beat.

757
00:38:37,060 --> 00:38:39,650
Kevin Hart completed our lap in...

758
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:42,490
1.50...

759
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:44,890
7.7, there you go.

760
00:38:44,940 --> 00:38:47,730
- Wow. - That's all right! - Top three.

761
00:38:47,780 --> 00:38:50,930
- You go third. - Top
three. - That's not bad.

762
00:38:50,980 --> 00:38:54,060
I'm happy with that. Top three.

763
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:58,050
Did you beat Anthony,
did Anthony beat you?

764
00:38:58,100 --> 00:39:01,650
Anthony Joshua, your time
around the Top Gear track

765
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:04,250
in the rallycross car, as our superstar,

766
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:06,290
one of our superstars, is...

767
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:09,090
1.50...

768
00:39:09,140 --> 00:39:12,210
2.6! You're the brand-new leader!

769
00:39:12,260 --> 00:39:16,290
- There he goes! There he goes! It's OK!
- What is this?!

770
00:39:16,340 --> 00:39:18,730
- You're beaten by the new champ! - No!

771
00:39:18,780 --> 00:39:21,370
- No, it's fine!
- No! No!

772
00:39:21,420 --> 00:39:23,690
- It's fine!
- No!

773
00:39:23,740 --> 00:39:27,100
- Let's hear it for Anthony
Joshua and Kevin Hart! - No!

774
00:39:31,140 --> 00:39:33,650
This is racism!

775
00:39:33,700 --> 00:39:37,250
This is racism at its best, right now!

776
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:40,180
He won because he's black!

777
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:45,730
Let's hear it again for Kevin
Hart and Anthony Joshua!

778
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:48,580
- You were moving!
- Very good.

779
00:39:53,900 --> 00:39:58,740
OK, our next film is about Rory
Reid and a little blue hatchback.

780
00:40:07,780 --> 00:40:11,930
This is the new Ford Focus
RS. It looks like a five-door

781
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:14,940
family hatchback that's been down the gym.

782
00:40:16,180 --> 00:40:19,680
Scratch the surface, though,
and it's got substance.

783
00:40:20,740 --> 00:40:24,730
A Cosworth-tuned 2.3-litre turbo engine

784
00:40:24,780 --> 00:40:27,380
that bangs out 345 horsepower.

785
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:30,340
345!

786
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:33,770
In a Ford Focus!

787
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:36,770
That's like fitting a
retirement bungalow with its own

788
00:40:36,820 --> 00:40:39,160
surface-to-air missile system!

789
00:40:40,820 --> 00:40:44,180
0 to 60 happens in 4.7 seconds.

790
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:48,770
Quicker than the Lamborghini
Countach ever managed it.

791
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:52,260
People, this isn't a Focus, it's a blur.

792
00:40:53,460 --> 00:40:57,530
And to prevent this blur becoming
a smear, it's got massive brakes

793
00:40:57,580 --> 00:41:00,660
and adaptive suspension to
cope with British B-roads.

794
00:41:01,980 --> 00:41:04,530
Even in its most unyielding setting,

795
00:41:04,580 --> 00:41:08,970
this isn't a hot hatch that's going
to grind your spine to talcum powder

796
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:11,810
the minute you see some bumpy tarmac.

797
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:14,610
The ride is firm, but it's forgiving.

798
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:17,220
And, more importantly, it's fast.

799
00:41:18,540 --> 00:41:20,250
And then there's the best bit.

800
00:41:20,300 --> 00:41:23,570
The Focus RS now has four-wheel drive.

801
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:26,690
That's not exactly revolutionary
in a modern hot hatch,

802
00:41:26,740 --> 00:41:29,280
but this version is a bit special.

803
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:37,570
Most four-wheel drive hot hatches
send pretty much all their power

804
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:39,490
to their front wheels,

805
00:41:39,540 --> 00:41:43,420
but the Focus RS sends 70%
of its power to the rear.

806
00:41:45,180 --> 00:41:48,770
Sensors monitor speed, yaw,
steering angle and G-force,

807
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:51,770
sending data to the rear drive
unit, where two clutch packs employ

808
00:41:51,820 --> 00:41:54,130
side-to-side torque
vectoring to send power

809
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:56,380
to the left or right wheel.

810
00:41:56,700 --> 00:41:58,450
You got all that?

811
00:41:58,500 --> 00:42:00,130
Me neither.

812
00:42:00,180 --> 00:42:02,770
But what it all adds up to is this button.

813
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:05,020
You press it four times...

814
00:42:05,500 --> 00:42:07,610
.. and this happens.

815
00:42:07,660 --> 00:42:09,810
Whoo!

816
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:11,580
Yeah!

817
00:42:15,020 --> 00:42:16,770
Whoo!

818
00:42:16,820 --> 00:42:19,420
Pointing forward is so last-century.

819
00:42:21,340 --> 00:42:24,140
Sideways! That's the new forwards.

820
00:42:26,820 --> 00:42:29,970
And if you're thinking,
"Well, that's immature,"

821
00:42:30,020 --> 00:42:32,060
yep, it is.

822
00:42:33,340 --> 00:42:36,220
But so am I!

823
00:42:38,740 --> 00:42:41,090
Drifting just makes everything better.

824
00:42:41,140 --> 00:42:43,410
Imagine how much happier
we'd be as a nation

825
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:46,140
if we could get everywhere like that.

826
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:51,290
And it's not because I've been
taking lessons off the Stig.

827
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:54,540
I haven't. Sliding this car is so easy.

828
00:42:55,660 --> 00:42:58,200
I reckon even a child could do it.

829
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:06,460
My granny could drift this.

830
00:43:09,340 --> 00:43:11,080
See what I mean?

831
00:43:12,980 --> 00:43:15,530
If I have to find a problem,

832
00:43:15,580 --> 00:43:18,130
the seating position is a little bit high,

833
00:43:18,180 --> 00:43:21,770
the gear change is a tiny
bit woolly around the edges,

834
00:43:21,820 --> 00:43:24,770
and from some angles the RS does look...

835
00:43:24,820 --> 00:43:26,170
tame.

836
00:43:26,220 --> 00:43:27,690
Sure, they're minor flaws,

837
00:43:27,740 --> 00:43:31,240
but the world of hot hatches
is cut-throat right now.

838
00:43:33,300 --> 00:43:37,450
Especially when it contains
bruisers like this,

839
00:43:37,500 --> 00:43:39,580
the Honda Civic Type R.

840
00:43:41,060 --> 00:43:44,690
Like the Focus, it costs £30,000,

841
00:43:44,740 --> 00:43:50,020
but unlike the Focus, it's all big
arches, big wing, big attitude.

842
00:43:51,180 --> 00:43:52,660
However...

843
00:43:55,420 --> 00:43:57,160
It looks great...

844
00:43:58,620 --> 00:44:03,020
.. and it drives OK, so why
does it feel a bit out of date?

845
00:44:06,580 --> 00:44:10,370
In the Ford Focus, your 30 grand
buys you four-wheel drive.

846
00:44:10,420 --> 00:44:13,220
In here, it's two for the price of four.

847
00:44:17,060 --> 00:44:19,530
There's more power than before...

848
00:44:19,860 --> 00:44:21,970
.. but it's all on the front wheels.

849
00:44:22,020 --> 00:44:24,360
And where's my drift button?!

850
00:44:25,540 --> 00:44:27,770
Even though it was only out last year,

851
00:44:27,820 --> 00:44:31,850
the Civic just feels old-fashioned,
like Honda have been so busy

852
00:44:31,900 --> 00:44:33,770
perfecting the old formula,

853
00:44:33,820 --> 00:44:36,410
they didn't notice that
the world's moved on.

854
00:44:36,460 --> 00:44:39,960
The game's become more
grown-up, more sophisticated.

855
00:44:40,340 --> 00:44:41,850
Uh-oh.

856
00:44:41,900 --> 00:44:44,410
I'm in serious trouble here.

857
00:44:44,460 --> 00:44:47,450
The Mercedes-AMG A45.

858
00:44:47,500 --> 00:44:51,890
Yep, the current kings of Formula
One have gone and built a hot hatch,

859
00:44:51,940 --> 00:44:54,730
and the results are... predictable.

860
00:44:54,780 --> 00:44:56,060
Go!

861
00:44:57,460 --> 00:44:58,980
No, no, no!

862
00:45:00,180 --> 00:45:02,380
It's just like Formula One!

863
00:45:03,140 --> 00:45:06,240
Honda, down on power,
languishing at the back.

864
00:45:08,740 --> 00:45:10,810
Civic, you've failed me!

865
00:45:12,340 --> 00:45:15,140
I like your look, but if I need power...

866
00:45:16,740 --> 00:45:18,850
.. I need the A45,

867
00:45:18,900 --> 00:45:22,650
with an engine developed
by Merc's F1 team.

868
00:45:22,700 --> 00:45:24,850
40 horsepower more than the Focus,

869
00:45:24,900 --> 00:45:26,970
70 more than the Civic,

870
00:45:27,020 --> 00:45:30,980
that's 376 horsepower
from a two-litre engine.

871
00:45:32,460 --> 00:45:34,330
Unprecedented.

872
00:45:34,380 --> 00:45:38,010
Like the Focus, the A45
also has four-wheel drive.

873
00:45:38,060 --> 00:45:40,570
It's got a fancy pants
double-clutch gearbox.

874
00:45:40,620 --> 00:45:43,130
It 0-60s in barely four seconds.

875
00:45:43,180 --> 00:45:47,060
And, with the limiter
removed, it'll hit 169mph.

876
00:45:48,260 --> 00:45:50,850
It's just as you'd expect from an F1 team,

877
00:45:50,900 --> 00:45:52,650
all very impressive...

878
00:45:52,700 --> 00:45:54,570
and all a bit dull.

879
00:45:54,620 --> 00:45:59,220
Look, here I am going round the
Hammerhead at serious speed.

880
00:46:01,380 --> 00:46:05,380
But you just don't feel as part of
the action as you do in the Focus.

881
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:16,810
This wins Top Trumps every time.

882
00:46:16,860 --> 00:46:19,730
Most power -- tick. Drag race -- tick.

883
00:46:19,780 --> 00:46:22,880
But who needs Top Trumps
if it's not exciting?

884
00:46:23,700 --> 00:46:25,440
Are you excited?

885
00:46:28,540 --> 00:46:30,570
I'll take that as a no.

886
00:46:30,620 --> 00:46:31,810
And that's the point.

887
00:46:31,860 --> 00:46:36,450
The A45 is just a bit
grown-up for a hot hatch.

888
00:46:36,500 --> 00:46:40,740
It's like... something
your dad might drive.

889
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:44,330
Here's the other kicker.

890
00:46:44,380 --> 00:46:49,890
This A45 is ten grand more expensive
than the Focus and the Type R.

891
00:46:49,940 --> 00:46:53,220
In hot hatch world, in
any world, that's a lot.

892
00:46:56,780 --> 00:46:59,250
Which is why I choose the Focus.

893
00:47:00,540 --> 00:47:04,250
Ten grand buys you 200 days'
worth of B-road petrol,

894
00:47:04,300 --> 00:47:07,180
or 50 tyres to turn into dust clouds.

895
00:47:08,380 --> 00:47:12,090
Even if it were the same price,
the RS is more interactive,

896
00:47:12,140 --> 00:47:15,250
more hands-on, more joyful.

897
00:47:15,300 --> 00:47:18,170
This is the best hot hatch on the planet.

898
00:47:19,460 --> 00:47:23,650
Maybe even the best fast
car you can buy, full stop.

899
00:47:23,700 --> 00:47:26,780
Keep your Ferraris, man, keep
your Porsches and your Paganis.

900
00:47:27,780 --> 00:47:29,850
I'm taking the Focus RS.

901
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:35,380
I love this thing. I do.

902
00:47:47,060 --> 00:47:50,930
And here they are, Rory Reid
and his little blue hatchback.

903
00:47:50,980 --> 00:47:53,690
That's a pretty hard sell you
gave the Focus there, Rory.

904
00:47:53,740 --> 00:47:57,010
But, seriously, "Keep your Paganis,
keep your Porsches," really?

905
00:47:57,060 --> 00:47:59,850
Really, really, man. This
car does the mundane,

906
00:47:59,900 --> 00:48:01,450
it does the astonishing.

907
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:04,530
You can take this to the shops,
you can drift it, you can race it.

908
00:48:04,580 --> 00:48:07,890
It's like having a three-car
garage in one car.

909
00:48:07,940 --> 00:48:10,930
Name me one other car
that's as much fun to drive.

910
00:48:10,980 --> 00:48:14,050
Your Paganis, your Porsches, all
the stuff you just said to keep.

911
00:48:14,100 --> 00:48:16,810
Yeah. I'm talking about in
the real world though, OK?

912
00:48:16,860 --> 00:48:21,330
On real roads, the Focus RS is just
more of a laugh, man, you know?

913
00:48:21,380 --> 00:48:24,490
It's more super than most supercars.

914
00:48:24,540 --> 00:48:25,810
Oh... You're sure?

915
00:48:25,860 --> 00:48:28,130
- Yeah, I said it! I said it!
- OK, OK.

916
00:48:28,180 --> 00:48:32,180
Ladies and gentlemen, Ford
salesman of the month, Rory Reid.

917
00:48:39,500 --> 00:48:41,050
So, not too long ago,

918
00:48:41,100 --> 00:48:44,050
I had a day off and I wanted to do
a bit of sightseeing around London.

919
00:48:44,100 --> 00:48:46,650
And, here's a little tip for
you, don't go with one of those

920
00:48:46,700 --> 00:48:48,090
open-top bus tours.

921
00:48:48,140 --> 00:48:50,330
You want to see London,
you're feeling brave,

922
00:48:50,380 --> 00:48:52,530
go with Top Gear Tours.

923
00:48:52,580 --> 00:48:54,120
Ask for Ken.

924
00:49:52,060 --> 00:49:54,250
- Ken?
- That's it.

925
00:49:54,300 --> 00:49:56,890
I don't think I... Do I need a helmet?

926
00:49:56,940 --> 00:49:59,940
- I would suggest it.
- All right, all right.

927
00:50:04,140 --> 00:50:05,570
OK, you know what I'm thinking...

928
00:50:05,620 --> 00:50:07,820
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

929
00:50:22,100 --> 00:50:24,570
I'm not in a big rush, you know.

930
00:50:39,500 --> 00:50:42,450
We can talk about some of
these sights I'd like to see.

931
00:50:42,500 --> 00:50:44,500
When you get a minute.

932
00:50:45,660 --> 00:50:48,370
I really want to see Buckingham Palace

933
00:50:48,420 --> 00:50:51,540
and I'd also like to see Tower Bridge.

934
00:50:53,140 --> 00:50:56,860
Oh, and the Houses of Parliament.
You know where that is?

935
00:51:01,180 --> 00:51:02,920
Oh, Canary Wharf!

936
00:51:06,820 --> 00:51:10,650
Did you know that that, right there,

937
00:51:10,700 --> 00:51:13,570
is the second tallest building in London?

938
00:51:15,420 --> 00:51:18,050
Yeah, that one over there.
Back there, way back there.

939
00:51:18,100 --> 00:51:19,780
That was it.

940
00:51:26,620 --> 00:51:30,410
- Whoa, whoa, wait a minute.
- What? What? - That's Tom Odell.

941
00:51:30,460 --> 00:51:32,210
♪ I wanna find... ♪

942
00:51:32,260 --> 00:51:35,560
- Who's that?
- Listen to him. Great piano player.

943
00:51:35,820 --> 00:51:37,890
- I can't hear anything.
- I can't hear anything.

944
00:51:37,940 --> 00:51:41,840
You know what, though? Let's
give him a little money. Here.

945
00:51:42,620 --> 00:51:45,220
- That's very nice of you.
- Yeah.

946
00:51:53,660 --> 00:51:56,000
Do you drink a lot of coffee?

947
00:52:03,340 --> 00:52:07,260
Oh, cool, Lloyds of London.

948
00:52:13,140 --> 00:52:14,810
Where we going?

949
00:52:15,380 --> 00:52:16,980
Secret route.

950
00:52:36,420 --> 00:52:37,610
What's this button do?

951
00:52:37,660 --> 00:52:39,450
- Don't.
- OK.

952
00:52:39,500 --> 00:52:41,460
Don't touch anything.

953
00:52:43,740 --> 00:52:45,740
Not touching anything.

954
00:52:57,340 --> 00:53:00,370
Do you know that most of
the London Underground

955
00:53:00,420 --> 00:53:02,700
is actually above ground?

956
00:53:09,780 --> 00:53:12,050
This is a good short cut.

957
00:53:14,580 --> 00:53:18,020
Oh, cool! This St Paul's Cathedral.

958
00:53:19,460 --> 00:53:21,800
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Turn around.

959
00:53:22,940 --> 00:53:24,610
Go round again.

960
00:53:24,660 --> 00:53:27,730
A lot of famous people get married here.

961
00:53:27,780 --> 00:53:30,170
Do they look familiar?

962
00:53:30,220 --> 00:53:31,960
Congratulations!

963
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:42,700
A fascinating city, really.

964
00:53:43,540 --> 00:53:46,970
Did you know that a lot of people
think this is London Bridge,

965
00:53:47,020 --> 00:53:49,650
but it's actually called the Tower Bridge,

966
00:53:49,700 --> 00:53:52,260
because of the, uh, the towers.

967
00:53:54,980 --> 00:53:56,720
Interesting, huh?

968
00:54:20,140 --> 00:54:22,340
Is this another short cut?

969
00:54:26,700 --> 00:54:28,640
This is interesting.

970
00:54:30,420 --> 00:54:32,410
Very colourful.

971
00:54:32,460 --> 00:54:35,460
- Least I could do.
- You're all right, Ken.

972
00:54:36,460 --> 00:54:38,400
Oh, look, look, look!

973
00:54:40,300 --> 00:54:42,290
What is that?

974
00:54:42,340 --> 00:54:45,900
- I think that is a Stigsy.
- Oh, cool!

975
00:54:46,980 --> 00:54:49,100
- Can I just...?
- No.

976
00:55:06,260 --> 00:55:08,330
Oh, Westminster Bridge!

977
00:55:14,420 --> 00:55:19,250
Did you know that it's illegal to
die in the Houses of Parliament?

978
00:55:19,300 --> 00:55:21,240
So maybe be careful.

979
00:55:32,380 --> 00:55:34,860
Oh. Does Winston approve?

980
00:55:36,260 --> 00:55:38,730
It doesn't look like it, does it?

981
00:55:38,980 --> 00:55:40,780
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

982
00:55:51,380 --> 00:55:53,980
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Slow down. Five-O.

983
00:55:57,460 --> 00:56:00,960
See the police right there?
They're right behind us.

984
00:56:01,380 --> 00:56:04,740
- Is this thing street legal?
- I think so.

985
00:56:09,700 --> 00:56:13,050
Did you know that if the flag
on top of Buckingham Palace

986
00:56:13,100 --> 00:56:16,460
is all the way at the top,
that means the Queen is home?

987
00:56:18,420 --> 00:56:21,730
